Text.SourceString: Waking up next to you this morning, as your husband, feels like a dream I never want to wake up from.
Text.LocalizedString: Waking up next to you this morning, as your husband, feels like a dream I never want to wake up from.

Text.SourceString: Our first day as a married couple... It's, uh... it's the start of our journey, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: Our first day as a married couple... It's, uh... it's the start of our journey, darling.

Text.SourceString: You looked absolutely stunning yesterday. And last night.
Text.LocalizedString: You looked absolutely stunning yesterday. And last night.

Text.SourceString: I wasn't sure what to get you, but I thought you might like this, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: I wasn't sure what to get you, but I thought you might like this, darling.

Text.SourceString: I wanted to make something special for you this morning. I hope you like it, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanted to make something special for you this morning. I hope you like it, darling.

Text.SourceString: Life on land is so different from the ocean depths. Each day here brings a new lesson, a new sight.
Text.LocalizedString: Life on land is so different from the ocean depths. Each day here brings a new lesson, a new sight.

Text.SourceString: Never thought I'd trade my trident for a hoe, but here we are.
Text.LocalizedString: Never thought I'd trade my trident for a hoe, but here we are.

Text.SourceString: You know, I never imagined I'd trade my fins for legs, but being here, with you, makes every step worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I never imagined I'd trade my fins for legs, but being here, with you, makes every step worth it.

Text.SourceString: Back underwater, decisions were clear, black and white. Here, it's different, more...nuanced. I'm learning that from you every day, my love.
Text.LocalizedString: Back underwater, decisions were clear, black and white. Here, it's different, more...nuanced. I'm learning that from you every day, my love.

Text.SourceString: I miss the ocean sometimes, the serenity of it. But I've found a different kind of peace here, with you, on our farm.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss the ocean sometimes, the serenity of it. But I've found a different kind of peace here, with you, on our farm.

Text.SourceString: We merfolk are not used to the changing seasons. It's fascinating, really.
Text.LocalizedString: We merfolk are not used to the changing seasons. It's fascinating, really.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I catch myself thinking about the sea's depths, but then I look around our farm, our home, and I know I made the right choice.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I catch myself thinking about the sea's depths, but then I look around our farm, our home, and I know I made the right choice.

Text.SourceString: This farm...you've done a remarkable job, my love. Your hard work truly shows.
Text.LocalizedString: This farm...you've done a remarkable job, my love. Your hard work truly shows.

Text.SourceString: Come here, darling. Let me give you a kiss.
Text.LocalizedString: Come here, darling. Let me give you a kiss.

Text.SourceString: Do you miss me?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you miss me?

Text.SourceString: I find the rhythms of farm life fascinating. The sunrise and sunset mark our days, not the ebb and flow of tides.
Text.LocalizedString: I find the rhythms of farm life fascinating. The sunrise and sunset mark our days, not the ebb and flow of tides.

Text.SourceString: But do you know who I find most fascinating? You, darling. Let me show you just how fascinating.
Text.LocalizedString: But do you know who I find most fascinating? You, darling. Let me show you just how fascinating.

Text.SourceString: There's a simplicity to farm life, I have to say, I like it.//<portrait=normal>It's quite a change from the royal courts underwater.
Text.LocalizedString: There's a simplicity to farm life, I have to say, I like it.//<portrait=normal>It's quite a change from the royal courts underwater.

Text.SourceString: I never realized how many textures there are on land. Feeling the earth under my feet, the grass, the mud – it's all so weird!
Text.LocalizedString: I never realized how many textures there are on land. Feeling the earth under my feet, the grass, the mud – it's all so weird!

Text.SourceString: The ocean will always be a part of me, with its depth and mysteries...just like you.//<portrait=happy>You'll always be a part of me, you pretty thing.
Text.LocalizedString: The ocean will always be a part of me, with its depth and mysteries...just like you.//<portrait=happy>You'll always be a part of me, you pretty thing.

Text.SourceString: Farming, it turns out, is more than just dirt and seasons. It's a sophisticated art.//I don't know how you do it, darling. You've mastered the art.
Text.LocalizedString: Farming, it turns out, is more than just dirt and seasons. It's a sophisticated art.//I don't know how you do it, darling. You've mastered the art.

Text.SourceString: Watching the seasons shift on land is captivating.
Text.LocalizedString: Watching the seasons shift on land is captivating.

Text.SourceString: Still getting used to being dry all the time.//Being dry 24/7 is new for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Still getting used to being dry all the time.//Being dry 24/7 is new for me.

Text.SourceString: The sun here really gets to you, doesn't it? I never knew thirst on land could feel this intense.
Text.LocalizedString: The sun here really gets to you, doesn't it? I never knew thirst on land could feel this intense.

Text.SourceString: Planning to make some cold treats later. Got any favorites, my love?
Text.LocalizedString: Planning to make some cold treats later. Got any favorites, my love?

Text.SourceString: I love you, darling. Just wanted to remind you, in case you forgot with all the stuff you've got going on today.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, darling. Just wanted to remind you, in case you forgot with all the stuff you've got going on today.

Text.SourceString: How's your day been, my love? I've been thinking about you.
Text.LocalizedString: How's your day been, my love? I've been thinking about you.

Text.SourceString: How's everything going today, my love?
Text.LocalizedString: How's everything going today, my love?

Text.SourceString: I miss you today.//Do you miss me? Show me how much.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss you today.//Do you miss me? Show me how much.

Text.SourceString: Hey, love. Just a reminder: you mean everything to me.//Don't ever leave me...I won't accept it.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, love. Just a reminder: you mean everything to me.//Don't ever leave me...I won't accept it.

Text.SourceString: Come here and let me hold you. I need to feel the love I've been missing all day.
Text.LocalizedString: Come here and let me hold you. I need to feel the love I've been missing all day.

Text.SourceString: How lucky am I to have you?
Text.LocalizedString: How lucky am I to have you?

Text.SourceString: I'm heading to Starlet Town. Need anything while I'm there?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm heading to Starlet Town. Need anything while I'm there?

Text.SourceString: I'm grabbing a coffee, love. Your usual order, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm grabbing a coffee, love. Your usual order, right?

Text.SourceString: How about a coffee break? I'll pick up our favorite brew.
Text.LocalizedString: How about a coffee break? I'll pick up our favorite brew.

Text.SourceString: I could use a tea boost. Want me to get you one too, hun?
Text.LocalizedString: I could use a tea boost. Want me to get you one too, hun?

Text.SourceString: Thinking of taking a walk through Starlet Town today. Come with me, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: Thinking of taking a walk through Starlet Town today. Come with me, darling?

Text.SourceString: I'll be at the library for a while. There's a book I've been wanting to check out.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll be at the library for a while. There's a book I've been wanting to check out.

Text.SourceString: Beach time today. Want to come along and catch some sun?
Text.LocalizedString: Beach time today. Want to come along and catch some sun?

Text.SourceString: Walking along the beach, I can almost hear the ocean's whispers. It's like a piece of home.
Text.LocalizedString: Walking along the beach, I can almost hear the ocean's whispers. It's like a piece of home.

Text.SourceString: I encountered a fox on the farm today. Such clever creatures.
Text.LocalizedString: I encountered a fox on the farm today. Such clever creatures.

Text.SourceString: I walked to the big tree this morning, just as the sun was rising. It's so peaceful there.
Text.LocalizedString: I walked to the big tree this morning, just as the sun was rising. It's so peaceful there.

Text.SourceString: I was thinking we could plan a trip to the Kingdom next weekend. Just you and me, away from everything.
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking we could plan a trip to the Kingdom next weekend. Just you and me, away from everything.

Text.SourceString: I'll take care of the house today. You've been working hard on the farm lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll take care of the house today. You've been working hard on the farm lately.

Text.SourceString: Do you know where the window cleaner is, darling?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know where the window cleaner is, darling?

Text.SourceString: I came across a sleeping bird near the mailbox this morning.//At first, I thought it was...well, I thought it was dead, so I was about to scoop it up, but then it just flew away.
Text.LocalizedString: I came across a sleeping bird near the mailbox this morning.//At first, I thought it was...well, I thought it was dead, so I was about to scoop it up, but then it just flew away.

Text.SourceString: Today, I spotted some rabbits on our farm. Are they ours, darling? They seemed quite at home.
Text.LocalizedString: Today, I spotted some rabbits on our farm. Are they ours, darling? They seemed quite at home.

Text.SourceString: I enjoy our nights together. Come to bed with me, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy our nights together. Come to bed with me, darling.

Text.SourceString: What are you in the mood for dinner? Let me cook something special for you, my love.
Text.LocalizedString: What are you in the mood for dinner? Let me cook something special for you, my love.

Text.SourceString: Should we watch TV? End the day easy?
Text.LocalizedString: Should we watch TV? End the day easy?

Text.SourceString: How's the farm today? Didn't give you much trouble, I hope?//My love doesn't deserve trouble for even a minute.
Text.LocalizedString: How's the farm today? Didn't give you much trouble, I hope?//My love doesn't deserve trouble for even a minute.

Text.SourceString: The sound of rain on the roof is soothing.
Text.LocalizedString: The sound of rain on the roof is soothing.

Text.SourceString: I've always wondered how rain felt on land. It's quite refreshing, actually.//And it smells incredible!
Text.LocalizedString: I've always wondered how rain felt on land. It's quite refreshing, actually.//And it smells incredible!

Text.SourceString: Snow is a curious thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow is a curious thing.

Text.SourceString: I'm still getting used to the cold of snow, but its beauty is undeniable...just like you.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm still getting used to the cold of snow, but its beauty is undeniable...just like you.

Text.SourceString: Snowflakes are fascinating.
Text.LocalizedString: Snowflakes are fascinating.

Text.SourceString: The sound of rain on the roof is soothing, darling.
Text.LocalizedString: The sound of rain on the roof is soothing, darling.

Text.SourceString: I've always wondered how rain felt on land. It's quite refreshing, actually.//And it smells incredible!
Text.LocalizedString: I've always wondered how rain felt on land. It's quite refreshing, actually.//And it smells incredible!

Text.SourceString: Joko was telling me about the forest creek yesterday. It sounds like a great spot for a swim.//What do you think about checking it out together sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: Joko was telling me about the forest creek yesterday. It sounds like a great spot for a swim.//What do you think about checking it out together sometime?

Text.SourceString: I ran into Poseidon at the beach recently. He was playing with Macy...that girl really loves him, I can tell.//<portrait=normal>Seeing him so happy there, it just brightened my day.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into Poseidon at the beach recently. He was playing with Macy...that girl really loves him, I can tell.//<portrait=normal>Seeing him so happy there, it just brightened my day.

Text.SourceString: Poseidon's living the high life with his fancy stroller and all the attention.//<portrait=normal>He's got it better here than in the barracks, no wonder he's not keen on going back. Can't say I blame him!
Text.LocalizedString: Poseidon's living the high life with his fancy stroller and all the attention.//<portrait=normal>He's got it better here than in the barracks, no wonder he's not keen on going back. Can't say I blame him!

Text.SourceString: I've seen some land dwellers in this clothing. I must say, it's pretty comfy.
Text.LocalizedString: I've seen some land dwellers in this clothing. I must say, it's pretty comfy.

Text.SourceString: These land-dweller outfits, I can feel the wind around my legs. They're very breezy.
Text.LocalizedString: These land-dweller outfits, I can feel the wind around my legs. They're very breezy.

Text.SourceString: These land-dweller outfits, I can feel the wind around my legs. They're very breezy.
Text.LocalizedString: These land-dweller outfits, I can feel the wind around my legs. They're very breezy.

Text.SourceString: I got these clothes from your Forest Keeper. He sold me this fine set for 20,000c, very cheap.
Text.LocalizedString: I got these clothes from your Forest Keeper. He sold me this fine set for 20,000c, very cheap.

Text.SourceString: The Forest Keeper told me that one should not cage one's feet, as they're not made to be caged.//<portrait=happy>I have to say, I agree. Ben is very wise indeed.
Text.LocalizedString: The Forest Keeper told me that one should not cage one's feet, as they're not made to be caged.//<portrait=happy>I have to say, I agree. Ben is very wise indeed.

Text.SourceString: Darling, do you know where my clothing set is, the one with the dolphin on it? I'm getting ready for Summer.//I hope you haven't thrown it out... I really like that one.
Text.LocalizedString: Darling, do you know where my clothing set is, the one with the dolphin on it? I'm getting ready for Summer.//I hope you haven't thrown it out... I really like that one.

Text.SourceString: Feel this fabric. I believe it was hand-colored. I'm not quite sure what that means, since I thought everything was made by hand.//<portrait=happy>But it does sound special.
Text.LocalizedString: Feel this fabric. I believe it was hand-colored. I'm not quite sure what that means, since I thought everything was made by hand.//<portrait=happy>But it does sound special.
